{
  "texts": [
    "Suppose (S, I, R, S *, I *, R *) is a solution of (3.1).We define new variables u = S -b δ, v = I, w = R, u * = S *, v * = I *, w * = R *.",
    "Thus, v (M) = (1-α)I+I * = (1-α)v+v * and n * = u * +v * +w *.",
    "Note that by nonnegativity guaranteed by theorem 3.1 as well as the total population bound of b/δ, we have that u ≤ 0, v, w, u *, v *, w * ≥ 0.",
    "Further the sum of any subcollection of the populations will be bounded by b/δ (e.g.",
    "u+ b δ + v + w ≤ b δ and u * + v * + w * ≤ b δ).In what follows, we use this total population bound several times without stopping to mention it.The new variables x = (u, v, w, u *, v *, w *) satisfydu = (-β(1 -α)(u + b δ)v (M) -µ(u + b δ)n * + νu * -δu)dt + (-σ β (1 -α) 2 v(u + b δ)) -σ µ (u + b δ)u *)dW dv = (β(1 -α)(u + b δ)v (M) -γv -µvn * + νv * -δv)dt + (σ β (1 -α) 2 v(u + b δ) -σ µ vv *)dW, dw = (γv -µwn * + νw * -δw)dt -σ µ ww * dW, du * = (-βu * v (M) + µ(u + b δ)n * -νu * -δu *)dt + (-σ β u * v * + σ µ (u + b δ)u *)dW, dv * = (βu * v (M) -γv * + µvn * -νv * -δv *)dt + (σ β u * v * + σ µ vv *)dW, dw * = (γv * + µwn * -νw * -δw *)dt + σ µ ww * dW,(4.3)We want to prove that the trivial solution of (4.3) is exponentially mean-square stable."
  ]
